# Dataset — Vehicle Damage Insurance Verification

This project uses the **Ripik Hackfest Vehicle Damage Dataset** from Kaggle.

## Download

🔗 [Kaggle Dataset Link](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/sudhanshu2198/ripik-hackfest)

You will need a free Kaggle account to download.

## Setup

After downloading, place the files in this folder as follows:

```
data/
├── train/
│   ├── images/          ← training images (.jpg)
│   └── train.csv        ← filename + label mappings
└── test/
    ├── images/          ← test images (.jpg)
    └── test.csv         ← filename mappings
```

## Label Mapping

| Label ID | Damage Class |
|----------|-------------|
| 2 | Scratch |
| 3 | Flat Tire |
| 4 | Dent |
| 5 | Window Broken |
| 6 | Lamp Broken |

## Dataset Statistics

| Class | Train Samples |
|-------|--------------|
| Scratch | 384 |
| Dent | 340 |
| Window Broken | 189 |
| Lamp Broken | 169 |
| Flat Tire | 70 |
| **Total** | **~1,152** |

> Note: The dataset has class imbalance. This was addressed using data augmentation during training.
